<xsd:schema xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" elementFormDefault="qualified" attributeFormDefault="unqualified" version="0.2" id="GMSv2_MetadataElements">
	<xsd:annotation>
		<xsd:appinfo>Schema metadata to follow when govtalk schema metadata has been updated to e-GMSv2. This is to prevent the inconsistency of using, in a schema intended for widespread normative use, e-GMSv1 metadata to describe a schema pertaining to e-GMSv2 metadata.</xsd:appinfo>
		<xsd:documentation>This schema document contains XML element declarations for e-GMS v2 metadata elements.  All the available elements are declared here, though very little is stated about their content. In practice,  further information about their content is likely to be specified in the schemas for local metadata standards.
The elements are listed here in the order in which they appear in the e-GMS document v2.0, with each element followed immediately by its subelements. 

Mostly, the element or subelement name as given in the e-GMS document has been used directly as the XML element or subelement name, with appropriate capitalisation. Some over-long names have been shortened (for example, in Rights subelements).

The CommonSimpleTypes schema published in the Address and Personal Details schema set is used to provide definitions of GDSC types. 
</xsd:documentation>
	</xsd:annotation>
